Here's a concise approach for runtime theme switching in .NET MAUI:

**1. Define resource dictionaries for each theme:**

```xml
<!-- Themes/LightTheme.xaml -->
<ResourceDictionary xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
                    xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml">
    <Color x:Key="PrimaryColor">#1A73E8</Color>
    <Color x:Key="BackgroundColor">#FFFFFF</Color>
    <Color x:Key="TextColor">#000000</Color>
    <!-- ... -->
</ResourceDictionary>
```

Create matching `DarkTheme.xaml` and `HighContrastTheme.xaml` with the same keys but different values.

**2. Create a theme service:**

```csharp
public enum AppTheme { Light, Dark, HighContrast }

public static class ThemeService
{
    public static void ApplyTheme(AppTheme theme)
    {
        var mergedDictionaries = Application.Current!.Resources.MergedDictionaries;
        mergedDictionaries.Clear();

        var themeDictionary = theme switch
        {
            AppTheme.Dark => new Themes.DarkTheme(),
            AppTheme.HighContrast => new Themes.HighContrastTheme(),
            _ => new Themes.LightTheme()
        };

        mergedDictionaries.Add(themeDictionary);

        // Persist the choice
        Preferences.Set("app_theme", theme.ToString());
    }

    public static void LoadSavedTheme()
    {
        var saved = Preferences.Get("app_theme", nameof(AppTheme.Light));
        if (Enum.TryParse<AppTheme>(saved, out var theme))
            ApplyTheme(theme);
    }
}
```

**3. Call on startup in `App.xaml.cs`:**

```csharp
public App()
{
    InitializeComponent();
    ThemeService.LoadSavedTheme();
}
```

**4. Settings page picker:**

```xml
<Picker x:Name="ThemePicker" Title="Theme"
        ItemsSource="{Binding Themes}"
        SelectedIndexChanged="OnThemeChanged" />
```

```csharp
void OnThemeChanged(object sender, EventArgs e)
{
    var selected = (AppTheme)ThemePicker.SelectedIndex;
    ThemeService.ApplyTheme(selected);
}
```

**5. Use `DynamicResource` (not `StaticResource`) in your XAML** so values update at runtime:

```xml
<Label TextColor="{DynamicResource TextColor}"
       BackgroundColor="{DynamicResource BackgroundColor}" />
```

**Key points:**
- `DynamicResource` is essential — it re-evaluates when dictionaries change.
- Keep the same keys across all three dictionaries for seamless switching.
- Use `Preferences` to persist the user's choice across sessions.
- Styles that reference theme colors should also use `DynamicResource` for inherited properties.
